Without explicit CORS settings, the app either blocks all cross-origin requests (breaking legitimate clients) or, if CORS middleware is added carelessly later, allows all origins.

**Recommendation:**
```js
const cors = require('cors');
app.use(cors({
  origin: ['https://yourdomain.com'],  // Whitelist specific origins
  methods: ['GET', 'POST'],
  allowedHeaders: ['Content-Type', 'Authorization'],
}));
```

